<br>
Kurns Tower!<br>
<br>
Now I know what your thinking. In FOB!? In Kunark!? Next to Cabalis!? Well, yes. This dungeon is GREAT XP. and here is how you do it.<br>
<br>
1. Stock up. Get your Level 12 spells. Especially Bind. Bags of your Level 16 spells and BAGS of components! Bags and Bags! Food you can summon weapons too (like you need em) Oh as for loot...There is only cash and bones to be had so FILL UP! I cant stress the importance of components!<br>
<br>
2. Head to Oasis and get on the barge. Once you hit land in the TD invis up and run to the dock &lt;keep near the shore/rocks to your right, you'll come across a few Ogres and the dock&gt; Once you out on the dock stay at the end and you'll be safe if Invis drops. Once the boat shows get on and get ready to jump off the left side.<br>
<br>
3. Ok your on the boat and zone into The Overthere. The second you zone in jump off and swim south to the shore. &lt;BE SURE you are not in the fort unless your a Dark Elf.&gt; Once you hit the shore run east till you get to the zone wall. Then south to the Warsilk Woods zone. &lt;About -0010 / -3500&gt; <br>
<br>
4. Now your in Warsilk Woods. Keep Invis up and run north to the shore. Once at the shore run east to the other side the south to the Field of Bone zone. &lt;About  3800/-2800&gt; Its a valley that heads south to the zone. {if you think you missed it head north}<br>
<br>
5. Finally, the Field of Bone! Head to loc  0800/-1000. You CANT miss this tower! Head up the ramp and Bind just outside.<br>
<br>
6. Zone in and RAPE skellies all day long. they are pushovers and they are all over! Often you will have the zone to your self a favorite spot, park your pet (horrendous pathing!) and pull to it. Water works well here cause these dummies never run anyway. Once the first floor greens out move up one...and up one and up one until your 20 and need to buy more spells.    <br>
<br>
<br>
Bumbahi<br>
